ALL this while I have omitted to ſpeak of that firſt and moſt wondrous Work of GOD, the Light: by which we ſee all other Things, and the eternal GODHEAD clearly in them, but leaſt of all is it ſeen it ſelf. Mr. Henry.
It is the great Beauty and Bleſſing of the Univerſe; and like the firſt-horn it doth of all Bodies moſt reſemble its great Parent, the Father of Light and Glory; in Purity, Brightneſs, Beneficence, and Spirituality;
for of all things viſible Light comes the neareſt to the Nature of a Spirit. There is nothing more excellent and admirable in the viſible Creation of GOD. An immenſe flowing Tide of Glory.
